<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--NewMadonna     04-30 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--New Madonna,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New York Artist Wins Contest to Create New Image of the Madonna</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A New York artist was named as the winner of a
nationwide contest to create a new image of the Madonna for
Chicago's oldest Roman Catholic Church.
   Bryan Hunt's entry, a pair of oil, pastel and graphite panels
titled ``Madonna and Child I and II,'' was selected as the best of
more than 400 entries sent by the nation's artists to Old St.
Patrick's Church.
   The Rev. Jack Wall, pastor of Old St. Patrick's, announced
Friday that Hunt's work was chosen from a field of 17 finalists by
a jury of art critics and curators, including a representative of
the church.
   ``We are very pleased with the jurors' selection,'' Wall said.
``We were seeking a dramatic way to relook at Mary in the Catholic
church, and we have found it in this winning piece.''
   As winner, Hunt will receive a purchase price of $10,000 for the
two panels, which each measure 22 by 33 inches.
</TEXT>
