<HEAD>Orioles Snap Losing Streak at 21</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Baltimore Orioles trounced the Chicago White
Sox 9-0 fpr their first win of the 3{-week-old season, snapping
their record-breaking losing streak at 21 games.
   The Orioles did it in style Friday night, allowing only four
hits and letting only one runner get past first base.
   Three cases of champagne were on ice and waiting for the Orioles
in their clubhouse afterward, the reward for the worst start in
major league history. The season opened April 4.
   Baltimore established the longest losing streak in American
League history with Thursday's defeat in Minnesota. They stopped
short of the major league mark of 23 consecutive losses by the
Philadelphia Phillies in 1961.
   The old record for the worst start in major league history was
held by both the 1904 Washington Senators and the 1920 Detroit
Tigers, who lost their first 13 games.
   A crowd of 14,059 sat quietly in 56-degree temperature as
Baltimore stopped its march of misery.
