<HEAD>Moscow State Circus Arrives For 14-Week British Tour</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seventy performers from the Moscow State Circus,
including a contortionist known as the ``Snake Girl,'' are in
Britain for the circus' first major tour in 20 years.
   The performers flew into London's Heathrow Airport on Friday for
a 14-week tour, which begins Sunday at Battersea Park in south
London and includes stops in other cities across the country.
   Vicki Charlton, chairman of the Entertainment Corp., organizers
of the tour, said a smaller version of the circus visited three
years ago, but a major tour has not been held for 20 years.
   Among the performers will be a two trapeze acts, high wire
performers, acrobats known as the Moscow Builders, and a Cossack
horse team.
