<HEAD>Police Say Ring Smuggled Cocaine, Hashish In Beef Carcasses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAGLIARI, Sardinia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Saturday they smashed a
narcotics ring that brought cocaine and hashish into Cagliari
hidden inside beef carcasses delivered to butchers.
   Police said eight people, mostly butchers, were in custody and
that three other people were sought. All are charged with
possession and sale of cocaine and hashish.
   The arrests came after an almost yearlong investigation, police
said.
   The Italian news agency ANSA said the ring had sold narcotics
worth hundreds of thousands of dollars.
   Police said the drugs were hidden in nylon bags stuffed inside
beef carcasses that were delivered in refrigerated trucks to
Cagliari, on the southern coast of the island of Sardinia.
