<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Hillerman,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Actor John Hillerman Bids Aloha to `Magnum P.I.'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor John Hillerman is ending an eight-year
run of fooling Britons playing Jonathan Higgins, the stuffy British
major-domo who runs the estate of the perpetually absent mystery
writer Robin Masters on ``Magnum P.I.''
   ``I get a lot of fan mail from England saying, `Well done, it's
good to see one of us making it.' I have to write back and say,
`Sorry to disappoint you, but I'm just a hick from Texas,'''
Hillerman said recently.
   The Texan bids aloha to the series in its final showing Sunday
night with a two-hour special episode in which the identity of the
unseen Robin Masters will be revealed.
   Of his eight years on the ``Magnum'' set, Hillerman said, ``I've
spent 33 years acting. I have done 23 motion pictures, and the last
eight years have been the happiest of my career.''

